        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "# pKa Values of Citric Acid (NIST SRD-46)\n\nCitric acid (2-hydroxypropane-1,2,3-tricarboxylic acid, **ligand_9058**) is a triprotic acid defined as **H₃L** in SRD-46. The database contains **48 measured equilibrium entries** across three stepwise protonation equilibria:\n\n| Step | Equilibrium | Beta Definition | Approximate pKa | # Measurements |\n|------|-------------|-----------------|-----------------|----------------|\n| pKa₁ | H₂L + H⁺ ⇌ H₃L | beta_def_53 | **~2.9** | 14 |\n| pKa₂ | HL + H⁺ ⇌ H₂L | beta_def_32 | **~4.35** | 14 |\n| pKa₃ | L + H⁺ ⇌ HL | beta_def_79 | **~5.65** | 20 |\n\nThe bracket pKa values from the ligand card are:\n\n| Dissociation | pKa (reference) |\n|--------------|-----------------|\n| H₃L → H₂L + H⁺ | **2.9** |\n| H₂L → HL + H⁺ | **4.35** |\n| HL → L³⁻ + H⁺ | **5.65** |",
